The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The value parameter 'stacksz' (type size_t) is modified in-place — e.g. the statement 'stacksz -= stacksz % POSIX_GlobalVars.PageSize;' (and earlier assignments like 'stacksz = PTHREAD_STACK_MIN;' and 'stacksz += ...') alter the function parameter. This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.8. Remediation: copy the parameter into a local variable and perform the arithmetic on that local variable instead of modifying the parameter.
